label: 1037 From Edward Lee [Louvain? winter 1519-20] [CWE]
further_annotation: Preface to Lee's *Annotationes in annotationes Novi Testamenti Desiderii Erasmi* (Paris: G. de Gourmont for K. Resch, [February 1520] = USTC 145174), cf. CWE VII, 117.

label: 104 To Prince Henry [Greenwich? autumn] 1499 [CWE]
further_annotation: Preface to *Prosopopoeia Britanniae*, first printed in *Collectanea adagiorum (I)* (Paris: J. Philippi, [ca. June-July] 1500 = USTC 201899), cf. CWE I, 195 and Tello 2023, no. 3.

label: 1055 To Ulrich von Hutten [Louvain? late 1519] [CWE]
further_annotation: The chosen date range is December 1519, which appears most probable in this context, considering events such as Erasmus's quarrel with Edward Lee, as detailed in CWE VII, 165.

label: 1581A To X [Basel, spring 1525] [CWE]
further_annotation: A probable terminus post quem is 21 March 1525, and a terminus ante quem is 25 August 1525, as outlined in CWE XI, 163.

label: 1634A From Benedetto Giovio [Como, summer? 1525] [CWE]
further_annotation: The terminus ante quem, 7 October 1525, is established by Ep. 1635. For the beginning of the date range, 1 June has been chosen, as suggested by CWE XI, 333.

label: 164 To Johann Poppenruyter Saint-Omer, [autumn] 1501 [CWE]
further_annotation: Dedication of the *Enchiridion militis Christiani*, first published in *Lucubratiunculae aliquot* (Antwerp: D. Martens, 15 February 1503 = USTC 400246), cf. CWE II, 51 and Tello 2023, no. 9.

label: 1925 To the Nuns of Denney [Basel, 1527 or 1528] [CWE]
further_annotation: Preface to *Epistola consolatoria in adversis* (Basel: Officina Frobeniana, [January-March] 1528 = USTC 653241), cf. CWE XIII, 515-516 and Tello 2023, no. 338.

label: 2417 From Frans Titelmans [Louvain? 1530] [CWE]
further_annotation: Preface to Titelmans' *Libri duo de authoritate libri Apocalypsis* (Antwerp: M. Hillen, 1530 = USTC 403828), cf. CWE XVII, 159.

label: 2418 To Udalricus Zasius [Freiburg, 1530–1] [CWE]
further_annotation: The beginning of the date range is anchored to the date of Pirckheimer's death on 22 December 1530, as referenced in ALLEN IX, 102.

recipient_as_marked: Adolph of Burgundy, heer van Veere [CWE]
label: 266 To Adolph of Burgundy, heer van Veere London, [autumn] 1512 [CWE]
2711 To William v, duke of Cleves Freiburg, 1532 [CWE]
further_annotation: Preface to two new books added to *Apophthegmata (II)* (Basel: H. Froben and N. Episcopius, 1532 = USTC 612553), cf. CWE XIX, 148 and Tello 2023, no. 410. The date range for this letter may be more specific, refer to ALLEN X, 89 for details.

label: 3031a From Konrad Heresbach Düsseldorf, 1534-6 [CWE]
further_annotation: The determination of the date range has been made in reference to ALLEN XI, 156.

label: 66 To Thomas Grey/Pierre Vitré [Paris? 1497?] [CWE]
further_annotation: Preface to an abbreviated version *De ratione studii* (Paris: G. Biermant and J. Granjon, 20 October 1511 = USTC 180591), cf. CWE I, 142 and Tello 2023, no. 27.

label: 676 To Alaard of Amsterdam Louvain, [1517] [CWE]
further_annotation: Preface to Erasmus' edition of *Eucherii de con temptu mundi* (Louvain: D. Martens, 1517 = USTC 403125), cf. CWE V, 137 and Tello 2023, no. 129.

label: 807 To Maarten Lips [Louvain, spring 1518?] [CWE]
further_annotation: A plausible date range is March to May 1518.

label: 811 To Gerard Geldenhouwer Louvain, [1518-19] [CWE]
further_annotation: CWE V, 38 establishes the terminus post quem as 12 April 1518. October 1519 has been selected as the end of the date range.

label: 842 To Helias Marcaeus [Cologne? 1518?] [CWE]
further_annotation: Preface to Erasmus' edition of *Iosephi de imperio rationis* (Cologne: E. Cervicornus, [May 1518] = USTC 657577), cf. CWE VI, 2 and Tello 2023, no. 137.

label: De Rodrigo Tous de Monsalve a Erasmo [Sevilla], [1533-1536] [Gil]
